<h2>Cut Vinyl vs. Printed Graphics</h2>
<p><strong>Cut vinyl lettering</strong> uses solid-color vinyl cut into individual letters and shapes. It's clean, professional, and extremely durable — lasting <strong>7–10 years</strong> outdoors. For simple text and single-color logos, cut vinyl is the most cost-effective and longest-lasting option.</p>
<p><strong>Printed graphics</strong> allow full-color logos, photos, and complex designs. We print on premium Avery Dennison cast vinyl with UV overlaminate for 5–7 years of outdoor durability. Best for multi-color logos and photographic elements.</p>

<h2>DOT Number Requirements</h2>
<p>The Federal Motor Carrier Safety Administration (FMCSA) requires <strong>USDOT numbers</strong> on both sides of all commercial vehicles that meet any of these criteria:</p>
<figure class="supp-image-block"><img src="/images/sns_roofing_truck.webp" alt="Vehicle lettering Chicago" loading="lazy" width="1200" height="420"><figcaption>Vehicle lettering Chicago — Chicago Fleet Wraps · (312) 597-1286</figcaption></figure>

<ul>
<li>Gross Vehicle Weight Rating (GVWR) over <strong>10,001 lbs</strong></li>
<li>Transporting <strong>hazardous materials</strong> requiring placards</li>
<li>Operating in <strong>interstate commerce</strong> for compensation</li>
</ul>
<p>Requirements: letters must be at least <strong>2 inches tall</strong>, in a color that contrasts with the vehicle's background, and visible from 50 feet. We ensure full FMCSA compliance on every DOT lettering job.</p>

